      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>The Norfolk and Petersburg Railroad was chartered in 1851
         and ran 81 miles between Norfolk, Virginia and Petersburg,
         Virginia. In 1870, it was consolidated with the Southside
         Virginia and Tennessee Railroad, and Virginia and Kentucky
         Railroad to form the Atlantic, Mississippi, and Ohio
         Railroad.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The information within this collection includes
         stockholders' and directors' minutes, financial ledgers and
         journals, cash books, construction accounts, and subject files
         relating to the operation of the Norfolk and Pertersburg
         Railroad Company.</p>
      </scopecontent>
